    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="202"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/256a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SERJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_HWA2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">u. s. urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-09">November 9,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1180. Secret and personal for the Ambassador from the Acting Secretary.</p>
                <p>The President has handed to me your message no. 6100 sent via Navy.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d202fn1">This is the telegram of November 6, <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_158">p. 158</ref>.</note> You are
                    authorized to comply with <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>’s
                    request that your letter containing the message concerning Turkey be made a part
                    of the secret military record of the Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Acting</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
